<article>
    <h1>A race to re&#xAD;mem&#xAD;ber</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201121/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-21"><time>2020-11-21</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Start­ing on Nov 26, adren­a­line junkies can chan­nel their in­ner race­course driver at the Dino Kart cir­cuit just out­side Ter­mi­nal 4’s Ar­rival Hall.</p>
    <p>The bat­tery-op­er­ated elec­tric Go-Karts can reach speeds of up to 24kmh.</p>
    <p>There are six Go-Karts on the adult track and five on the chil­dren’s track through­out the day. Visi­tors get to choose rac­ing slots with their ac­tiv­ity passes.</p>
    <p>Just next to Dino Kart, open­ing on Dec 3, is Dino Fest, Sin­ga­pore’s first di­nosaur­themed car­ni­val mar­ket with 50 stalls of­fer­ing street food, fes­tive-themed mer­chan­dise and in­ter­ac­tive ac­tiv­i­ties.</p>
    <p>Info: Till Dec 31. Spend and re­deem ac­tiv­ity passes at a dis­counted price for ev­ery $30 spent ($80 for su­per­mar­kets) with a max­i­mum of four ac­tiv­ity passes in a sin­gle re­ceipt at pub­lic ar­eas at Ter­mi­nals 1, 3 and 4 or Jewel Changi Air­port. For more in­for­ma­tion, go to www.changifes­tivevil­lage.com</p>
    <p>Reach speeds of up to</p>
    <p>24kmh on these bat­tery­op­er­ated elec­tric Go-Karts (above).</p>

